   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER TWO THE DIVINE ECONOMY</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>AND THE SATANIC CHAOS 2 Scripture Reading: John 1:1, 14; Rev 21:1-3; 22:1-2, 16-21 OUTLINE In the New Testament: Concerning Christ and His ministry: The divine economy with Christ as the God-man: Christ as the embodiment of the Triune God became incarnated to be a God-man John 1:1, 14; Luke 1:26-38; Matt 1:18-23.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>John the Baptist came out to testify concerning Christ Matt 3:1-12; John 1:6-8, 15, 19-36.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The seekers of Messiah came to Christ and followed Him John 1:37-49; Matt 4:17-24; John 3:1-15.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Christ taught the kingdom, proclaimed the gospel, and healed all kinds of diseases, attracting a great crowd to follow Him Matt 4:23-25.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Christ revealed to His followers the kingdom of the heavens Matt 5 7 , the mysteries of the kingdom of the heavens Matt 13 , Christ and the church Matt 16:13-19 , the consummation of this age and the second coming of Christ Matt 24 25 , and the mystery of the Divine Trinity in union with the believers of Christ John 14 17 .</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>The satanic chaos with the Romans, the Jews, and the followers of Christ: Herod sought to kill Christ in His babyhood Matt 2:1-22.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The Pharisees criticized and blasphemed Christ Matt 9:10-13, 33-34; 12:22-35.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>The people of Israel rejected Christ and His teaching Matt 11:20-24; 13:53-58.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>The Pharisees and Sadducees tempted Christ and instructed people with teachings of leaven Matt 16:1-12.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Satan moved in Peter to frustrate Christ from carrying out His crucifixion Matt 16:21-26.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>The followers of Christ contended with one another to be great Luke 22:24; Matt 20:21-27.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>One of Christ's followers, Judas, betrayed Christ Luke 22:21-23, 47-48 ; another one, Peter, denied Him three times under Satan's sifting Luke 22:31-34, 54-62 ; and the rest, as sheep, were scattered Matt 26:31 .</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>The Jews collaborated with the Roman government to sentence Christ to death and crucify Him Luke 23:1-43.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>The divine economy in Christ's crucifixion, resurrection, and ascension: God judged Christ on the cross for the sin of the world and for the sin of the believers John 1:29; 1 Cor 15:3 , and Christ died an all-inclusive vicarious death John 19:34; 12:24 .</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>The women followers of Christ watched His crucifixion Matt 27:55-56.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>Joseph, one expecting the kingdom of God, and the women followers of Christ buried Christ in an excellent way Luke 23:50-56; Matt 27:57-61.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>The followers of Christ discovered His resurrection and received the revelation that Christ in His humanity was born in His resurrection to be the firstborn Son of God with His many brothers constituting His Body Matt 28:1-10; John 20:1-18; Acts 13:33; Rom 8:29; Heb 2:11-12.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>Christ in His resurrection taught His eleven apostles concerning the kingdom of God for forty days Acts 1:3.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>The disciples of Christ saw His ascension Acts 1:9-11.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>The satanic chaos with the chief priests, the Pharisees, and the elders: The chief priests and Pharisees sent soldiers to guard the grave of Christ and sealed the stone Matt 27:62-66.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>The chief priests and the elders bribed the guarding soldiers to say that while they were sleeping in the night the disciples of Jesus stole His body away Matt 28:11-15.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>In the ministry of the apostles: The divine economy: Peter and about one hundred twenty disciples gathered together and prayed in one accord for ten days Acts 1:12-15.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>The Spirit was poured out upon the one hundred twenty disciples of Christ on the day of Pentecost Acts 2:1-4, 17-18.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>Peter preached at Pentecost, and three thousand repented, believed, and were baptized in the name of Jesus Christ, and later five thousand Acts 2:14-41; 4:4.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>The believers continued steadfastly in the teaching and the fellowship of the apostles, in the breaking of bread and the prayers, having all possessions common and increasing with new believers day by day Acts 2:42-47; 4:32-37.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>The word of God grew, and the number of the disciples multiplied greatly Acts 6:7; 12:24; 19:20.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>The disciples were scattered from Jerusalem to preach the gospel throughout the regions of Judea and Samaria Acts 8:1, 4.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>The gospel spread under Peter's ministry Acts 9:32-43.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>The gospel, through Paul's ministry, spread to the Gentile world, and many churches were raised up Acts 13 28.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>The churches raised up through Paul's ministry were strengthened and corrected under John's ministry 1, 2, 3 John and Revelation.</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>The satanic chaos: The Jewish religion and the Roman government persecuted the apostles and the church Acts 4:1-3, 5-6; 7:57 8:3; 12:1-4; 16:22-24.</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>Ananias and Sapphira deceived the Spirit and were punished to death Acts 5:1-11.</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>The Jews rejected the apostles' preaching and persecuted the apostles Acts 13:45-46, 50; 14:2, 5, 19; 17:13; 18:12-13; 19:9; 20:3; 21:27-36.</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>The Judaizers stressed circumcision among the believers Acts 11:1-3; 15:1-2.</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>Peter and Barnabas became weak in keeping the truth of the gospel Gal 2:11-14.</S>
   <S PAR='37' RSNT='1' SNO='37'>Barnabas separated himself and his work from Paul Acts 15:36-39.</S>
   <S PAR='38' RSNT='1' SNO='38'>The church in Corinth had divisions, fornication, and lawsuits 1 Cor 1:10-13; 11:18-19; 5:1; 6:1, 6-8 , questioned the apostleship of Paul 9:1-3 , and condemned Paul of being crafty, saying that he took advantage of them by guile 2 Cor 12:16-18 .</S>
   <S PAR='39' RSNT='1' SNO='39'>The Jewish preachers of the gospel preached the gospel in rivalry with Paul Phil 1:15-17.</S>
   <S PAR='40' RSNT='1' SNO='40'>The Judaizers, as dogs, evil workers, the concision, and false brothers, stole into the churches Phil 3:2; Gal 2:4.</S>
   <S PAR='41' RSNT='1' SNO='41'>Gnostics came in to carry the believers off through their philosophy according to the tradition of men and the elements of the world and not according to Christ Col 2:8.</S>
   <S PAR='42' RSNT='1' SNO='42'>The teaching of different things other than God's economy in faith was carried on 1 Tim 1:3-4.</S>
   <S PAR='43' RSNT='1' SNO='43'>The winds of teaching in the sleight of men, in craftiness, invaded the churches Eph 4:14.</S>
   <S PAR='44' RSNT='1' SNO='44'>Division-makers rose up Rom 16:17.</S>
   <S PAR='45' RSNT='1' SNO='45'>Factious sectarian men existed in the churches Titus 3:10.</S>
   <S PAR='46' RSNT='1' SNO='46'>The two sister co-workers, Euodias and Syntyche, were in discord Phil 4:2-3a.</S>
   <S PAR='47' RSNT='1' SNO='47'>James and the elders in Jerusalem exhorted Paul to keep the ordinances of the Jewish law Acts 21:18-26.</S>
   <S PAR='48' RSNT='1' SNO='48'>Some, as Hymenaeus and Alexander, thrust away faith and a good conscience and became shipwrecked regarding the faith 1 Tim 1:19-20; cf.</S>
   <S PAR='49' RSNT='1' SNO='49'>4:1-2.</S>
   <S PAR='50' RSNT='1' SNO='50'>All the believers in Asia turned away from Paul's ministry 2 Tim 1:15.</S>
   <S PAR='51' RSNT='1' SNO='51'>Some, as Hymenaeus and Philetus, misaimed concerning the truth, saying that the resurrection had already taken place 2 Tim 2:17-18.</S>
   <S PAR='52' RSNT='1' SNO='52'>Demas loved the present age and abandoned the apostle Paul 2 Tim 4:10a.</S>
   <S PAR='53' RSNT='1' SNO='53'>Alexander the coppersmith did many evil things to the apostle Paul 2 Tim 4:14-15.</S>
   <S PAR='54' RSNT='1' SNO='54'>In Paul's first defense no one was with him to support him, but all abandoned him 2 Tim 4:16-17.</S>
   <S PAR='55' RSNT='1' SNO='55'>Some went beyond and did not abide in the teaching of Christ 2 John 9-11.</S>
   <S PAR='56' RSNT='1' SNO='56'>Diotrephes loved to be first in the church and did not receive the apostles 3 John 9-10.</S>
   <S PAR='57' RSNT='1' SNO='57'>Some went in the way of Cain, rushed out in the error of Balaam for reward, and perished in the rebellion of Korah Jude 11-13.</S>
   <S PAR='58' RSNT='1' SNO='58'>Among the seven churches in Asia in Revelation 2 and 3, the first one lost her first love toward the Lord 2:4 ; the third one fell into the world where Satan's throne is, held the teaching of Balaam involved with idolatry and fornication, and held also the teaching of the Nicolaitans related to hierarchy 2:13-15 ; the fourth one had the teaching of Jezebel involved with fornication, idolatry, and the deep things of Satan 2:20, 24a ; the fifth one was living in name, yet she was dead, with nothing perfect before God 3:1-2 ; and the last one, in Laodicea, was lukewarm, boasting in her "riches," but not realizing her wretched, miserable, poor, blind, and naked condition, with the Lord Christ standing outside and knocking at her door 3:14-17, 20 .</S>
   <S PAR='59' RSNT='1' SNO='59'>The ending of the satanic chaos and the consummation of the divine economy: The satanic chaos will end with the termination of the evil Satan, the old creation, and all the negative things in the lake of fire Rev 20:9 21:1, 8; 22:15.</S>
   <S PAR='60' RSNT='1' SNO='60'>The divine economy will be consummated with the processed Triune God, the new creation, and the holy city of living water Rev 21 22.</S>
   </TEXT>
